        <abstract> 
<p>Comments on A. W. Bennett’s letter [<hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> 1 (1869): 58] on fertilisation of winter-flowering plants. CD used net, not a bell-glass to cover <hi rend="italic">Lamium</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Refers to F. Delpino’s observations on fertilisation of grasses; CD is glad to say these observations are compatible with "the very general law that distinct individual plants must be occasionally crossed".</p>
        </abstract>
